<WindowDeviceorientationabsolute_event>
<summary>
The <strong><c>deviceorientationabsolute</c></strong> event is sent to the <c>ondeviceorientationabsolute</c> event handler on a <see cref="'Window'"/> event when absolute device orientation changes.
</summary>
<remarks>
<para>This event is not cancelable and does not bubble.</para>
<para>-<see cref="Window.Deviceorientation_event"/><br/>-<see cref="DeviceOrientationEvent"/><br/>-<see cref="Window.Deviceorientation_event"/> event<br/>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Device_orientation_events/Detecting_device_orientation">Detecting device orientation</see><br/></para>
<para><seealso href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Window/deviceorientationabsolute_event"> <em>See also on MDN</em> </seealso></para>
</remarks>
</WindowDeviceorientationabsolute_event>
